===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[blak]]'', from Old English ''[[blæc]]''. Cognates include '''[[blaze]]''', '''[[bleach]]''', '''[[blond]]''', '''[[bald]]''', '''[[bale]]'', '''[[pale]]''', Latin ''[[flagare]]'', to shine, Latin ''[[blancus]]'', white, Gothic ''[[𐌱𐌰𐌻𐌰]]'' (bala), paleness, German ''[[erbleichen]]'', bleich, go -, turn pale, German ''bleichen'', bleach and Russian ''[[веля]]'', white

